arts.ttl: Bromley boss pleased with on-loan Millwall winger Mayor’s debut
arts.sum: The Millwall loanee has joined for the rest of the League Two season in an effort to get some game time. Bromley are on a run of five games in the league without a win.

arts.ttl: Lloyd’s performance earns praise as QPR lose at Millwall
arts.sum: Luke Cundle headed in a debut goal before half-time to earn Millwall victory, but Calm saw enough from Lloyd to suggest he merited a starting berth ahead of Michael Frey and Rayan Kolli. The 21-year-old scored just his second goal for the club to level the game at the Den after Aaron Connolly had given the home side a first minute lead.

arts.ttl: Will Millwall make more signings before Monday’s transfer deadline? Lions boss Neil has his say
arts.sum: The Lions have had a busy week with two notable additions made – Luke Cundle and Camiel Neghli. Alex Neil has not ruled out Millwall making more additions to their squad before Monday’s transfer deadline.

arts.ttl: QPR assistant boss asked about absence of Sheffield United-linked defender Jimmy Dunne
arts.sum: When asked about Dunne’s absence, Calm said: “Jimmy Dunne had a small problem in the groin two days ago and in the end we have picked the players we had available for the game.” QPR assistant head coach Xavi Calm claimed that injury was the reason for defender Jimmy Dunne’s absence in Saturday’s 2-1 defeat to Millwall.

arts.ttl: Dunne had groin problem – QPR assistant boss Calm
arts.sum: Xavi Calm said Jimmy Dunne had a groin problem after the defender missed QPR’s 2-1 defeat at Millwall. Dunne was absent amid interest from Sheffield United. West London Sport revealed on Friday that Rangers had rejected an offer from the Blades but negotiations between the two clubs are ongoing ahead of Monday’s transfer deadline. arts.ttl: The lowdown on Millwall 2 QPR 1 - Cundle enjoys dream start to Lions career and Connolly looks a shrewd signing
arts.sum: Alex Neil’s side produced some nice approach play after scoring again but didn’t overly trouble Paul Nardi in the visiting goal, while QPR upped the ante in a bid to grab a share of the spoils. QPR made changes in the second half in search of an equaliser and went close when Sam Field’s deflected strike had Lukas Jensen backpedalling, but the Lions keeper made a fine stop.

arts.ttl: Luke Cundle goal sees Millwall beat QPR for third successive win
arts.sum: It was a first league win at The Den under boss Alex Neil.

arts.ttl: Dunne left out of QPR side amid Sheffield United interest
arts.sum: Jimmy Dunne has been left out of the QPR side for today’s match against Millwall amid interest from Sheffield United in the defender.
